# 1. Domain-Driven Design — Bounded Contexts & Aggregates

*The domain is decomposed into six bounded contexts. "PDM Field Data Collection" is the Core Domain (the reason the system exists); Identity & Access and Location Reference Data are Supporting/Generic subdomains; Reporting & Analytics is a read-only (CQRS) query side over the core domain's data; the two Phase 2 contexts are documented for roadmap completeness only.*

## 1. Identity & Access Management (IAM)

**Supporting Domain Manages** authentication and the lifecycle of User accounts (Administrators and Data Collectors). Enforces that Data Collectors are always created by an Admin (no self-registration) and that role-based capabilities (submit forms vs. manage platform) are respected.

**Aggregate Root: User**

**Value Objects:**

- PhoneNumber — validated Uganda phone format, used as login identifier; unique across all Users
- PasswordHash — one-way hashed credential, never exposed outside the aggregate
- Role — enum { ADMIN, DATA_COLLECTOR }
- AccountStatus — enum { ACTIVE, DEACTIVATED }

**Invariants:**

- PhoneNumber must be unique across all Users.
- A User with role DATA_COLLECTOR can never be created without an authenticated ADMIN actor as creator (created_by_admin_id required).
- A DEACTIVATED User cannot authenticate, online or offline.
- Only ADMIN-role Users may create, deactivate, reactivate, or reset the password of another User.

**Domain Events:**

- DataCollectorAccountCreated(userId, createdByAdminId)
- AdministratorAccountCreated(userId, createdByAdminId)
- UserDeactivated(userId, byAdminId)
- UserReactivated(userId, byAdminId)
- PasswordReset(userId, byAdminId)
- UserAuthenticated(userId, channel: ONLINE|OFFLINE)

**Domain Services:**

- PasswordPolicy (hash/verify via out port)
- AuthenticationTokenIssuer (issues JWT access+refresh via out port)

