## 2. PDM Field Data Collection

**Core Domain** The heart of the system: capturing structured survey responses (BYP, IYP, LGO, Parish Chief) from a Respondent, recorded by an authenticated Data Collector, with strict per-financial-year uniqueness and offline-first submission semantics. This is where the business rules from FORM-*, UNIQ-* and SYNC-* live.

**Aggregate Root: Submission**

**Entities:**

- Respondent — demographic/location details of the interviewee (name, phone, gender, ageGroup, location); child entity, 1:1 with its Submission
- SurveyResponse (abstract) — one concrete subtype per form type, child entity, 1:1 with its Submission: BypResponse | IypResponse | LgoResponse | ParishMonitoringResponse

**Value Objects:**

- FormType — enum { BYP, IYP, LGO, PARISH_MONITORING }
- SubmissionStatus — enum { PENDING, SYNCED, FLAGGED, DUPLICATE }
- FinancialYearPeriod — value object derived from a date: {year, half: H1|H2}, H1 = Jan1--Jun30, H2 = Jul1--Dec31
- DeviceSubmissionId — client-generated idempotency key (UUID) so the same offline record is never double-created on retry
- GeoRef — {districtId, subCountyId, parishId, villageId}
- AgeGroup / Gender — controlled-vocabulary enums
- SubmissionProvenance — {collectorId, submittedAt, deviceId}

**Invariants:**

- A Submission always has exactly one Respondent and exactly one SurveyResponse whose subtype matches its FormType.
- submitted_by must reference a User with role = DATA_COLLECTOR and status = ACTIVE at time of submission.
- Age on Respondent must be >= 15 (rejected otherwise).
- (Respondent.phoneNumber, FormType, FinancialYearPeriod) must be unique among Submissions with status in {PENDING, SYNCED} — enforced by RespondentUniquenessPolicy both client-side (pre-submit) and server-side (on sync).
- A second submission that violates uniqueness is not rejected outright but transitions to status = FLAGGED (DUPLICATE) for Admin review, never silently merged or dropped.
- DeviceSubmissionId is unique — replaying the same offline record on retry must not create a duplicate row.

**Domain Events:**

- SubmissionReceivedByServer(submissionId, formType, deviceSubmissionId)
- SubmissionSynced(submissionId, syncedAt)
- DuplicateSubmissionFlagged(submissionId, conflictingSubmissionId)
- RespondentUniquenessViolationDetected(phoneNumber, formType, period)

**Domain Services:**

- RespondentUniquenessPolicy — encapsulates the (phone, formType, period) uniqueness rule; used identically by the client (pre-submit check against local cache) and server (authoritative check on sync)
- ConditionalFieldValidator — encapsulates each form's Given/When/Then conditional-visibility & required-field rules (FORM-09)
- FinancialYearPeriodCalculator — derives the current/any FinancialYearPeriod from a date

