# 3. Hexagonal Architecture — Package & Class Structure

*The backend (Spring Boot 4.x / Java 21) follows Ports & Adapters. The domain package has zero framework dependencies. The application package implements the domain's inbound ports (use cases). Everything under adapters is a replaceable detail: REST controllers are one inbound adapter, JPA/Redis/JWT/export libraries are outbound adapters implementing domain-defined outbound ports. This keeps the core survey/eligibility rules testable without Spring, a database, or HTTP.*

